item.description:
Ok, that post title is deliberately provocative. Twitter and all that.
So look, we&rsquo;re designed this advanced PowerShell class. One of the top five constant suggestions I get whenever I say &ldquo;advanced&rdquo; and &ldquo;PowerShell&rdquo; is &ldquo;.NET Framework.&rdquo;
And I get it. When there&rsquo;s no cmdlet, .NET has a ton of goodies that can solve a lot of problems. Maybe you don&rsquo;t like turning to it, but you&rsquo;ll do it if you have to.
